Usage: get_path_groups [-help] [<patterns>] [-include_internal_groups]
                       [-nocase] [-regexp]

-help                        # Prints out the command usage
<patterns>                   # Creates a collection of path groups whose name
                             # matches one or more of the specified patterns
                             # (string, optional)
-include_internal_groups     # Include internal path groups considered by tool
                             # (bool, optional)
-nocase                      # Pattern matching is not case sensitive
                             # (bool, optional)
-regexp                      # Treats the specified patterns a a regular
                             # expression pattern (bool, optional)